    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-07-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-07-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="401"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d401">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756.5–MAP/7–951: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Indonesia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-07-13T18:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 13, 1951—6 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>65. Urtel 29 July 9.<note n="1" xml:id="d401fn1">In telegram 29 from Djakarta,
                        July 9, Ambassador Cochran reported that he had been informed that
                        Ambassador Sastroamidjojo had been instructed to ask for reimbursable
                        military aid for the Indonesian National Police (756D.5–MAP/7–951).</note>
                    <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Amb has not requested reimbursable mil aid
                    for <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> under Sec 408 E <gloss
                        target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss>.</p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Emb has requested priority assistance (DO
                    rating) on nr contracts for mil forces. However, pending inclusion rubber by
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> in list goods considered covered by
                        <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> res Dept has neither taken extraordinary
                    efforts to prevent nor extraordinary efforts to assist in procurement goods in
                    US. Under this policy Dept has for some time withheld approval priority
                    assistance for number <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> contracts with US
                    firms. When satis response assured Dept notified Munitions Board its <pb
                        facs="0705" n="687" xml:id="pg_687"/> approval issuance necessary DO’s 825
                    radio sets (SCR–694) for <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> Army. These
                    orders in process issuance. Dept also urging favorable consideration DO covering
                    industrial hand tools, 35 battery chargers, 20 water clarators (purifiers), 150
                    motorcycles and 75 sets motorcycle spare parts. Two orders tires and tubes and
                    126,000 feet subterranean telephone cable being actively studied. Separate tel
                    fol on subject tires.<note n="2" xml:id="d401fn2">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
